Disk Forensics > [T6]: Windows MRULists: Tracking User's Recent Actions

(2) MRULists

Windows registry includes a set of keys called MRULists, which stand for "Most Recently Used" lists and are responsible for keeping track of a user's recent actions. For example, when you open the "run" window and start typing, a dropdown menu will appear with the most recently used commands you entered earlier. The same goes for recent URLs you typed in a browser, and recent documents you opened. Etc.

MRU list for "run"

 

MRULists are helpful for forensic analysts because they provide two valuable pieces of information. The first is a list of files and commands each user accessed, and the second is in which order. You may be wondering, how?

Each user account has its own NTUSER.DAT registry hive (where MRULists are stored) located at C:\Users\<user>\NTUSER.DAT. For example, analyzing NTUSER.DAT located at "C:\Users\adam\NTUSER.DAT" and inspecting corresponding MRULists will show the user "adam" accessed files. This way, you can check the MRUList of a particular user.

MRULists stores items ordered from most recent to oldest. Meaning, you can draw a timeline of actions a specific user performed (.e.g., opened file X first, then file Y, then file Z...etc.).

 

Common MRU keys are:

  • Microsoft Office MRUs: Documents recently opened by Microsoft Office Suite.
    • Software\Microsoft\Office\15.0\<Office application>\File MRU
    • Software\Microsoft\Office\15.0\<Office application>\Place MRU
  • Windows shell dialog box: Files opened or saved using the windows shell dialog box
    • Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Explorer\ComDlg32\OpenSavePidlMRU\*
  • Windows Explorer: Files recently opened by Windows Explorer.
    • Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Explorer\RecentDocs
  • Start -> RUN dialog: entries executed using "run" window.
    • Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Explorer\RunMRU
  • Path Bar: Entries typed manually in Windows explorer PathBar
    • Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Explorer\TypedPaths

 

Recent objects accessed via "Run" - (zoom in)

  1. RunMRU key.
  2. RunMRU key path.
  3. The MRUList value (fedcba) shows the order in which the user accessed these objects. It translates to:
    • The item in the "a" row (C:\Users\IEUser\Desktop\1) is the oldest accessed object.
    • The item in the "f" row (eventvwr.exe\1) is the most recently accessed object.
  4. A list of the most recent objects accessed via "run".
